"```sql\nSELECT circuits.name AS circuit_name, circuits.location, races.name AS race_name\nFROM circuits\nJOIN races ON races.circuitId = circuits.circuitId\nWHERE circuits.country = 'USA' AND races.year = 2006;\n```\n\nThis SQL query selects the name and location of circuits in the USA that hosted Formula 1 races in 2006, along with the name of the race each circuit hosted. It uses a join between the `circuits` and `races` tables based on the `circuitId` foreign key relationship."